## 📌 Project Overview

This project demonstrates the design of a simple PCB for interfacing an **LED** with an **Arduino UNO** using **KiCad**.

The PCB includes an LED connected through a current-limiting resistor to one of the Arduino digital pins. It is an ideal beginner project for learning schematic capture, PCB layout, routing, and footprint placement.

