## ⚙️ Working Principle

1. Arduino UNO provides power to the circuit.
2. A digital output pin drives the LED.
3. The 1 kΩ resistor limits current to protect the LED.
4. When the output pin is HIGH, the LED turns ON.
5. When the output pin is LOW, the LED turns OFF.

